  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Choice for Women Cho&apos;rti&apos;s</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Outcome 1: The women of the families in the community have cash available to meet the food needs of their families.
Output 1.1 : Households experiencing food insecurity have been identified, according to selection criteria.
Output 1.2 : A cash voucher system has been agreed and established with the community.
Output 1.3 : The women of beneficiary households receive financial assistance to meet the needs caused by the drought</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to help 265 women and indigenous Cho&#xB4;rti&#xB4;s families of Las Flores community, Jocot&#xE1;n Township, Chiquimula department in eastern Guatemala, which are suffering food shortages, crop losses and other drought. Using the methodology of Cash Transfer via checks aimed primarily at household managers: women, during three months that will ensure action.

Within the project aims to define a learning process on the elements that allow proper implementation of the methodology, to provide in the present and future humanitarian interventions, based on the principles of human dignity and effective help.</narrative>
  </description>
